 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udacraftman.showPublicProfile?language=EN>dacraftman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/14/01 2:02:27 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: To be a wizard?</span><hr size=1> bump <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udanenel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Danenel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/14/01 2:15:15 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: To be a wizard?</span><hr size=1> I found at level 16 is when I first went &quot;Whoa&quot; when I saw the damage of a new spell (level 16 Lightning Bolt which actually at level 51, I STILL use!). Stick it out till 16 and then see what you think.<br>
<br>
As for items Get a Savants Cap/Batfang Headband for 3INT/3WIS ... they are like 25 to 40pp depending on server. Get a Braided Cinch Cord (4INT) for your belt for around 300pp. Other slots will be fairly expensive to fill so I don't bother with potential items.<br>
<br>
-Danenel Plasmweaver<br>
L51 Wizard, Tholuxe Paells<br>
Gathering of Ancients<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/urealwing.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Realwing</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ultradbz.net/buttons/mybutton.jpg BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/14/01 2:18:29 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: To be a wizard?</span><hr size=1> I am level 52 and i love being a wiz if thats what you mean, can't imagine playing something else. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udacraftman.showPublicProfile?language=EN>dacraftman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/14/01 2:40:01 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: To be a wizard?</span><hr size=1> i guess ill stick it out to 16. (should be there in less then 2 days i hunt at the sirens) i only have like 100pp cause i spent it all on a dagger of frost, is it really that good? so i figure ill save the money for my spells, then i'll try to get more money. im really hoping that my guild can raid kurn's tower for a possible solist's icy wand. I am only 1 of 2 wizards in my guild, and the other wizzy (only level 30) has the wand already. hehe any tips on getting one? am i high enough to try to get one?<br>
<br>
my main concern with wizzies are all those rants i see about them. is it really that bad? i mean at my level i already see the problem with finding groups, and the downtime during soloing is horrible. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaeaostarwind.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aeao Starwind</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/14/01 4:36:05 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: To be a wizard?</span><hr size=1> Stick with it till atleast level 20. At about the level you are now I got kinda leary but decided to just keep with it until about 20, then I knew definitly it was the right class for me.<br>
<br>
<br>
On the wand;<br>
<br>
Best place in Kurns to try for one is in the 'mines' area. At your level you won't survive down there without a group, most things will con white to red and if you get introuble it's a pretty hard run to the zoneout. Took me about 8 hours of clearing the area for my wand to drop.<br>
<br>
<br>
Drop me a e-mail at  aeao@djkeoki.com  and i'll give you some advice that'll help you with the camp.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udacraftman.showPublicProfile?language=EN>dacraftman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/15/01 9:27:33 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: To be a wizard?</span><hr size=1> bump<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uorsmoxlorr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Orsmo Xlorr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/15/01 9:44:27 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: To be a wizard?</span><hr size=1> The dagger is something that you can put in your range slot and still get the +int bonus.  16 was a nice damage upgrade and at 20 with world gates that is when I realized this is sweet.  Screw the groups.  I also only get to play a few hours a week and still manage to level just fine.  But you have to be smart about it.  At levels 12 to 20 I was in Kurn's tower.  For the kunark and dungeon XP bonus's.  20 to 24 i was in the Lake of Ill Omen. 24 to 27 I was in Mistmoore doing yard trash.  27 to 40 I was in cyrstal Caverns.  Notice a pattern?  Dungeons give an XP bonus but require a different plat style.  So I try to Max out the XP I get per kill.<br>
<br>
As for the rants, I think alot of those are people who have been playing this game for awhile and have seen so much get nerfed and changed that it has made them bitter.  Mind you now when I log on and do my first /auction I start getting tells to see if I'm grouped.  Am I so good a wizard?  Yes but also I have been working on my PC faction from day one.  <br>
<br>
So I say play the wizard up to the level where you find it no longer fun and move on to the next class.  What level will that be?  No clue, because for me everytime I get new spells I seem to have a whole new character again.<br>
<br>
Orsmo Xlorr<br>
45 lvl Wizard<br>
