rtitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/16/01 1:51:33 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re:to be a wizard</span><hr size=1> Imho, NO... <p><img src=http://members.home.net/mtw333/Misc/Alaadin2.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uelaurieldragonstorm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elauriel Dragonstorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/16/01 4:28:54 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re:to be a wizard</span><hr size=1> It all depends on what you want to do friend.  I think that playing only 5-10 hours per week, you will not have time to make lots of friends or do much leveling at higher levels.  However, if you enjoy casual play and like the wizard's abilities, you can solo quite effectively after you get your AoE snare spell.<br>
<br>
Dagger of Frost has a decent int boost, great cold resist (+20),and is quite a good weapon actually, so I would hold on to it personally.  <br>
<br>
Good Luck!<br>
